               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donor and his family members; name of the king; a few lines (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page of Texts I and II; two or three initial lines of sections of Texts I and II; donation note (fol. 32rb); name of the protagonist of Text II; some phrases and words in Text I; some corrections (e.g., fols. 13ra l.1, 15rb l.7); names of the weekdays (entire or elements) in Text I;  elements of punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="32ra"/>Fol. 32ra-b: ተፈጽመ፡ ድርሳነ፡ መድኃኒነ፡ በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ በዘመነ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ ኃይለ፡ ሥላሴ…<foreign xml:lang="en">Fol. 32ra-b: The homily of Our Saviour was completed in the peace of God in the time of our King Ḫaylä Śǝllase…</foreign>
                        <note>The colophon mentions King Ḫaylä Śǝllase I (r. 1930-74).</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
